This paper is likely to belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category as it discusses the QUIC protocol, which is a transport layer protocol used for internet communication. It may also belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) category as it mentions the TLS protocol, which is used for secure communication. Additionally, it could be classified under Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) as it discusses the implementation of QUIC on multiple servers. It may also fall under Software Engineering (cs.SE) as it proposes and implements a test suite for QUIC. Finally, it could be classified under Programming Languages (cs.PL) as it discusses the features of different implementations of QUIC.
